of the country.

1303
01:26:10,337 --> 01:26:11,839
-I didn't mean to--
-I know.

1304
01:26:13,106 --> 01:26:14,341
I know.

1305
01:26:15,075 --> 01:26:16,310
You were protecting me.

1306
01:26:19,379 --> 01:26:20,881
I didn't mean
to fall for you.

1307
01:26:24,484 --> 01:26:26,119
Well, welcome to the human race.

1308
01:26:27,554 --> 01:26:28,755
[soft music]

1309
01:26:31,992 --> 01:26:33,827
Why do people fall in love?

1310
01:26:37,331 --> 01:26:38,665
Love, huh?

1311
01:26:40,534 --> 01:26:41,635
No shit.

1312
01:26:43,237 --> 01:26:44,304
Yeah, Ricky will get you
a ride,

1313
01:26:44,371 --> 01:26:45,706
you just got to get out
of here.

1314
01:26:46,940 --> 01:26:48,141
I'm not running.

1315
01:26:50,244 --> 01:26:51,879
They'll go after you
one way or another.

1316
01:26:52,312 --> 01:26:54,047
I can't let you take
the rap for me.

1317
01:26:54,581 --> 01:26:55,749
I'm okay!

1318
01:26:56,450 --> 01:26:57,885
They won't put me away.

1319
01:27:00,521 --> 01:27:01,622
[car horn]

1320
01:27:16,170 --> 01:27:17,504
[officer] Copy that. Let's go.

1321
01:27:30,184 --> 01:27:31,351
[officer]
Out of the way, please.

1322
01:27:33,320 --> 01:27:34,655
Thank you.

1323
01:27:46,667 --> 01:27:48,001
[Russell]
Damn it, Jenny.

1324
01:27:48,535 --> 01:27:49,736
Are you okay?

1325
01:27:51,038 --> 01:27:52,039
Yeah.

1326
01:27:54,074 --> 01:27:55,075
Who were these guys?

1327
01:27:57,411 --> 01:27:59,880
A drug dealer, a gun runner,

1328
01:28:00,714 --> 01:28:02,082
his bodyguard.

1329
01:28:04,184 --> 01:28:05,552
Where's your parolee?

1330
01:28:10,224 --> 01:28:12,192
Look, I told you everything
that I know.

1331
01:28:13,961 --> 01:28:15,162
He saved my life.

1332
01:28:16,930 --> 01:28:18,599
I got knocked out
in the madness,

1333
01:28:19,233 --> 01:28:21,001
and when I came to,
he was gone.

1334
01:28:31,278 --> 01:28:32,713
He tried to get out
of the action

1335
01:28:32,779 --> 01:28:33,881
and they went after them.

1336
01:28:45,926 --> 01:28:47,694
Well, you haven't given up
after all.

1337
01:28:48,562 --> 01:28:49,563
Oh.

1338
01:28:57,938 --> 01:28:59,339
Come on, let's go.

1339
01:29:02,376 --> 01:29:03,510
[Spanish music]

1340
01:29:38,712 --> 01:29:39,880
[birds singing]

1341
01:30:03,136 --> 01:30:05,005
[Henri] Embrace the tiger.

1342
01:30:07,808 --> 01:30:09,343
Return to the mountain.

1343
01:30:11,945 --> 01:30:12,946
Henri?

1344
01:30:17,784 --> 01:30:19,453
What the hell
are you doing here?

1345
01:30:21,421 --> 01:30:22,956
I decided to stop running.

1346
01:30:25,659 --> 01:30:27,361
Only way to get past it
is to pay up.

1347
01:30:28,996 --> 01:30:30,497
Only way to see you again.

1348
01:30:32,099 --> 01:30:33,433
Well, they gave you a break.

1349
01:30:35,269 --> 01:30:36,336
A break?

1350
01:30:36,904 --> 01:30:39,473
Well, you led me to Stewart
and you saved my life

1351
01:30:39,540 --> 01:30:42,242
so they're going to give
you a year for the gun

1352
01:30:43,076 --> 01:30:44,278
and breaking parole.

1353
01:30:45,479 --> 01:30:47,014
-A year?
-Mm-hm.

1354
01:30:50,450 --> 01:30:51,451
That's great!

1355
01:30:53,687 --> 01:30:54,688
Thanks.

1356
01:30:55,289 --> 01:30:56,290
Sure.

1357
01:30:57,658 --> 01:30:59,860
Hm, well...

1358
01:31:01,461 --> 01:31:02,963
Do we have to do it right now?

1359
01:31:03,664 --> 01:31:05,098
Can we spend a little time?

1360
01:31:05,899 --> 01:31:07,968
[chuckles]
The sooner you're in,

1361
01:31:08,035 --> 01:31:09,269
the sooner you're out.

1362
01:31:10,604 --> 01:31:12,272
That's what I love
about the outside.

1363
01:31:12,673 --> 01:31:14,408
Never enough time
for anything.

1364
01:31:14,474 --> 01:31:15,776
[ending music]

